	<div class = "container aboutText span7">
		<hr>
		<p> The India Cultural Association (ICA) is a non-profit organization dedicated to enhancing Indian Cultural Awareness in Portland, Oregon. The Association was established in 1980, and has since brought the entire Indian community together, and provided a venue for a population of over 10,000 to reconnect with it's roots.</p>
		<br>
		<p> ICA's claim to fame is it's largest and most-loved event -- The India Festival. The festival is filled with the tastes, sights, and sounds of India, with live music, dance, food and entertainment thoughout the day! The festival brings over 8,000 visitors to Portland's Pioneer Square, and never fails to delight with its non-stop entertainment. </p>
		<br>
		<p>We at ICA are so thankful to the Portland community for making our organization what it is today. If you would like to learn more about us or leave a message, please look to our "Contact Us" page!</p>
